cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.NI, cs.DC 

The paper focuses on detecting cyberattacks in mobile cloud computing, which is a security issue. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed framework leverages a deep learning approach, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses experimental results, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper deals with mobile cloud computing, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
